data.12: Range - Geographic delineations established by public land survey, often six miles on the latitudinal axis
data.13: Section - Geographic delineations established by public land survey, often one mile square
data.14: Quarter Section - Geographic delineations established by public land survey, often 1/2 mile square portion of a "section"
data.27: Marker Type - Identifies type of facility
data.32: Aliquot - Identifies the subdivided portion of a one square mile legal survey area section
data.43: Principal Meridian - A starting point of a rectangular land survey area
data.47: Quarter Quarter Quarter Section - The subdivided description for a usual ten-acre portion of a legal survey area section
data.48: Quarter Quarter Section - The subdivided description for a usual forty- acre portion of a legal survey area section
data.58: Universal Transverse Mercator Quadrant - A designation of a rectangular survey area used for large scale mapping
data.A: Jurisdiction to Receive Credit for Uniform Commercial Code Filing
data.AP: All Points - Qualifies a code that identifies a geographic area where transportation rates apply
data.BL: Government Bill of Lading Office Code (GBLOC) - Qualifies a code that identifies the location of a government office authorized to process transportation bills of lading
data.EL: Employer Location - A specific work location where an injury occurred
data.FI: Federal Information Processing Standards (FIPS) 55 (Named Populated Places)
data.FR: U.S. Custom's Facilities Information and Resource Management Systems (FIRMS)
data.FT: Foreign Trade Zone - A secured area legally outside a nation's customs territory, usually located in or near customs ports of entry, industrial parks or terminal warehouse facilities; while in a zone, merchandise is not covered by a customs bond or subject to duty or excise tax
data.FV: Free Alongside Vessel (Free On Board [F.O.B.] Point)
data.IA: International Air Transport Association (IATA) Location Qualifier
data.IT: Intermediate FOB Point - A location indicating the point of destination is not the origin or final destination but rather at some other point
data.OF: Other Unlisted Free On Board (FOB) Point - An FOB Point that cannot be predetermined
data.OL: Open and Prepay Station List Code(SCAC & Number)
data.OP: Other Unlisted Acceptance Point - An acceptance Point that cannot be predetermined
data.PA: Port of Arrival - Port where shipment enters country
data.PB: Port of Discharge - Port where shipment is unloaded
data.PE: Port of Entry - Port where customs is declared
data.RA: Rate Area Code - Qualifies a code that identifies a geographic area where transportation rates apply
data.RE: Regional Education Service Agency - An educational agency funded by a state or by school districts for the purpose of providing services to multiple schools or school districts
data.RG: Region Code - Qualifies a code that identifies a geographic area where transportation rates apply
data.ZN: Zone Code - Qualifies a code that identifies a geographic area where transportation rates apply
